definitions.definition: To trip or fall ; to walk clumsily .
examples: Last night, you drunkenly stumble d to the front door, waking up the whole house.

definitions.definition: To make a mistake or have trouble .
examples: I always stumble over verbs in Spanish.

definitions.definition: To cause to stumble or trip.
To mislead ; to confound ; to cause to err or to fall.
To strike or happen (upon a person or thing) without design; to fall or light by chance; with on , upon , or against .

main_definition: ( intransitive ) To trip or fall ; to walk clumsily .
secondary_definitions: ( intransitive ) To make a mistake or have trouble .
( transitive ) To cause to stumble or trip.
( transitive , figurative ) To mislead ; to confound ; to cause to err or to fall.
To strike or happen (upon a person or thing) without design; to fall or light by chance; with on , upon , or against .
